{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["Unsupported OS: iOS","Unsupported OS: macOS","Unsupported OS: visionOS","Unsupported OS: watchOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"text","text":"object "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Passcode"}],"languages":["data"]}]},{"kind":"properties","items":[{"required":false,"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"true"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":", the system prevents use of a simple passcode. A simple passcode contains repeated characters, or increasing or decreasing characters, such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"123"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CBA"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"name":"allowSimple","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"false"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", the system causes a password reset to occur the next time the user tries to authenticate. If this key is set in a device profile, the setting takes effect for all users, and admin authentications may fail until the admin user password is also reset. Available in macOS 10.13 and later."}]}],"name":"changeAtNextAuth","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies a regular expression, and its description, used to enforce password compliance. Use the simpler passcode restrictions whenever possible, and rely on regular expression matching only when necessary. Mistakes in regular expressions can lead to frustrating user experiences, such as unsatisfiable passcode policies, or policy descriptions that don’t match the enforced policy."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Available in macOS 14 and later.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"customRegex","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"Passcode.CustomRegex","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"mdm-profiles:Passcode.CustomRegex","identifier":"doc://com.apple.devicemanagement/documentation/DeviceManagement/Passcode/CustomRegex-data.dictionary"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"value":"false","kind":"default"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":", the system forces the user to enter a PIN.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"forcePIN","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"boolean","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"11"},{"kind":"minimum","value":"2"},{"kind":"maximum","value":"11"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The number of allowed failed attempts to enter the passcode at the device’s lock screen. After four failed attempts, the system imposes a time delay before a passcode can be entered again. The delay increases with each attempt. In macOS, set ","type":"text"},{"code":"minutesUntilFailedLoginReset","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to define a delay before the next passcode can be entered. When this number is exceeded in macOS, the system locks the device; in iOS, the system wipes the device.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"maxFailedAttempts","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"integer"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The maximum grace period, in minutes, to unlock the phone without entering a passcode. The default is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":", which is no grace period and requires a passcode immediately. In macOS, the system translates this grace period value to screen-saver settings."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"maxGracePeriod","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"minimum"},{"value":"15","kind":"maximum"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The maximum number of minutes for which the device can be idle without the user unlocking it, before the system locks it. When this limit is reached, the system locks the device and the passcode is required to unlock it. The user can edit this setting, but the value can’t exceed the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"maxInactivity"},{"type":"text","text":" value."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In macOS, the system translates this inactivity value to screen-saver settings. The maximum value for macOS is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"60"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Setting this key removes the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"never"},{"text":" option in the Settings UI on user enrolled devices.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"maxInactivity","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"value":"1","kind":"minimum"},{"value":"730","kind":"maximum"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The number of days for which the passcode can remain unchanged. After this number of days, the system forces the user to change the passcode before it unlocks the device.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"maxPINAgeInDays","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"0"},{"kind":"minimum","value":"0"},{"kind":"maximum","value":"4"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The minimum number of complex characters that a passcode needs to contain. A "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"complex","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" character is a character other than a number or a letter, such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"&"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"%"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system ignores this property for user enrollments."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"minComplexChars","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"},{"value":"0","kind":"minimum"},{"value":"16","kind":"maximum"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The minimum overall length of the passcode. This value is independent of the value for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"minComplexChars"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"name":"minLength","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The number of minutes before the system resets the login after the maximum number of unsuccessful login attempts is reached. This key requires setting "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"maxFailedAttempts"},{"type":"text","text":". Available in macOS 10.10 and later."}]}],"name":"minutesUntilFailedLoginReset","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"value":"1","kind":"minimum"},{"value":"50","kind":"maximum"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This value defines ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"N"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", where the new passcode must be unique within the last ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"N","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" entries in the passcode history.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"pinHistory","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}]},{"required":false,"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"false"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the system requires alphabetic characters instead of only numeric characters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"requireAlphanumeric","introducedVersion":"4.0.0","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}]}],"title":"Properties"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Specify ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.mobiledevice.passwordpolicy"},{"text":" as the payload type.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The presence of this payload type prompts an iOS or macOS device to present the user with a passcode entry mechanism. The complexity of the passcode can be customized with this payload."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In iOS user enrollments, the system allows the Passcode payload type, but ignores all keys. Instead, the presence of the Passcode payload forces these settings:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"allowSimple","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" = "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forcePIN"},{"text":" = ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"minLength","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" = "},{"code":"6","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Profile-availability","level":3,"text":"Profile availability","type":"heading"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Device channel","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS, macOS, visionOS, watchOS"}]}]],[